<subSubSection id="24CB1080FFAFFFF1FAB2AC0F82CDFB5B" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFAFFFF1FAB2AC0F8128FBB7" blockId="27.[151,1437,685,1107]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAFFFF1FAB2AC0F815EFC9F" bold="true" box="[199,315,865,891]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previous records from the coast of 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFAFFFF1F8A1AC0F8322FC9F" box="[724,839,865,891]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
include São Sebastião (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFAFFFF1FE2DAC0F849BFC9F" author="Holthuis, L. B." box="[1112,1278,865,891]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 292" refId="ref64998" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1991) Marine lobsters of the world. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of interest to fisheries known to date. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, 125 (13), 1 - 292." type="journal article" year="1991">Holthuis 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFAFFFF1FF7EAC0F8096FC7B" author="Dall'Occo, P. L. &amp; Bento, R. T. &amp; Melo, G. A. S." pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="47 - 52" refId="ref60319" refString="Dall'Occo, P. L., Bento, R. T. &amp; Melo, G. A. S. (2007) Range extensions for lobsters off the Brazilian coast (Crustacea, Decapoda, Palinura, Astacidea). Biociencias, 15, 47 - 52." type="journal article" year="2007">
Dall’Occo 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAFFFF1FFFDAC0C80D1FC7B" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
—REVIZEE, st. 1129, São Sebastião, 
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFAFFFF1F8D5ACE8829CFC45" box="[672,761,902,929]" degrees="24" direction="south" minutes="55" orientation="latitude" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" precision="925" value="-24.916666">24°55′S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFAFFFF1F975ACE88306FC45" box="[768,867,902,929]" degrees="44" direction="west" minutes="33" orientation="longitude" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" precision="925" value="-44.55">44°33′W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFAFFFF1F91AACEB8395FC7B" box="[879,1008,901,928]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.13" metricValueMax="6.21" metricValueMin="6.05" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="613.0" valueMax="621.0" valueMin="605.0">605–621 m</quantity>
, 
<date id="186F65CBFFAFFFF1F98EACEB8411FC7B" box="[1019,1140,901,927]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="2002-04-19">19.iv.2002</date>
, 
<specimenCount id="7AD78882FFAFFFF1FE0AACEB84BDFC7B" box="[1151,1240,901,927]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="male">2 males</specimenCount>
, MZUSP 15252). 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFAFFFF1FAE2ACC7813EFC27" authorityName="Spence Bate" authorityYear="1888" box="[151,347,937,963]" class="Malacostraca" family="Nephropidae" genus="Nephropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosea">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAFFFF1FAE2ACC7813EFC27" box="[151,347,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Nephropsis rosea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found at great depths from 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFAFFFF1F8C3ACC78301FC27" box="[694,868,937,963]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" metricValueMax="12.6" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="840.0" valueMax="1260.0" valueMin="420.0">420 to 1,260 m</quantity>
in mud or fine sand substrate, and it is not fished in 
<collectingCountry id="14C6039BFFAFFFF1FAC0ACA38099FC03" box="[181,252,973,999]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and considered rare (Silva 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAFFFF1F84DACA082E3FC03" box="[568,646,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al. 2</emphasis>
007; Santana 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAFFFF1F954ACA0833FFC03" box="[801,858,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
2016). We suggest that the absence of 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFAFFFF1FF60ACA08516FC03" box="[1301,1395,974,999]" class="Malacostraca" family="Nephropidae" genus="Nephropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosae">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAFFFF1FF60ACA08516FC03" box="[1301,1395,974,999]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">N. rosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFAFFFF1FFF6ACA0809CFBEF" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1880" class="Malacostraca" family="Nephropidae" genus="Nephropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agassizii">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAFFFF1FFF6ACA0809CFBEF" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">N. agassizii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFAFFFF1FB5BAC9C81CBFBEF" authorityName="S. I. Smith" authorityYear="1881" box="[302,430,1009,1035]" class="Malacostraca" family="Nephropidae" genus="Nephropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeata">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAFFFF1FB5BAC9C81CBFBEF" box="[302,430,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">N. aculeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the material sampled herein is due to their restriction to waters deeper than 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFAFFFF1FF66AC9F8528FBEF" box="[1299,1357,1009,1035]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="40.0">40 m</quantity>
, where we did not concentrate our sampling efforts. Even though we sampled at depths of up to 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFAFFFF1FE0AAB7B84ADFBCB" box="[1151,1224,1045,1071]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="130.0">130 m</quantity>
, it was not enough to capture them.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFAFFFF1FAE2ABCB82CDFB5B" blockId="27.[151,680,1189,1215]" box="[151,680,1189,1215]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFAFFFF1FAE2ABCB82CDFB5B" bold="true" box="[151,680,1189,1215]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Infraorder 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFAFFFF1FB51ABCB81E1FB5B" authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1979" box="[292,388,1189,1215]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraOrder="Axiidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="infraOrder">Axiidea</taxonomicName>
de Saint Laurent, 1979
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
